### ==========================================
### End-to-End Choreography Chain (Lesson 12)
### Order → Payment → Inventory → Notification
### ==========================================
###
### Prerequisites:
###   docker compose up -d      (RabbitMQ + Mongo)
###   Start all four sidecars (see docs/commands.md)
###
### Watch the four terminals — you should see, in order:
###   order-service        : published OrderCreated
###   payment-service      : Received OrderCreated → published PaymentCompleted
###   inventory-service    : Received PaymentCompleted → published InventoryReserved
###   notification-service : Received InventoryReserved → EMAIL SENT, SMS SENT

POST {{orderService}}/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "orderId": "ORD-777",
    "amount": 250
}

###
### Verify each service's Mongo collection now has a document
### (orders, payments, inventory).

###

### ==========================================
### Dead Letter Topic (Lesson 14)
### ==========================================
###
### Any orderId starting with "FAIL-" triggers a permanent failure
### inside payment-service. Dapr will:
###
###   1. Deliver OrderCreated to payment-service (attempt 1) → throws
###   2. Retry via `pubsubInboundRetry` policy (attempts 2..4)
###   3. After maxRetries=3, forward the CloudEvent to the
###      `payment-failed` dead letter topic
###   4. payment-service's DLQ subscription logs it (see terminal)
###
### Watch payment-service terminal for the [DLQ] block.

POST {{orderService}}/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "orderId": "FAIL-500",
    "amount": 999
}

###

### ==========================================
### Transactional Outbox Chaos Test (Lesson 15)
### ==========================================
###
### The /orders/chaos endpoint calls createOrder() then throws.
### Response is HTTP 500, but the sidecar has already transactionally
### committed both the state save AND the OrderCreated publish.
###
### Expected:
###   - HTTP response       : 500 with "Simulated crash AFTER save..."
###   - Redis (orderstore)  : key `ORD-CHAOS-1` exists
###   - RabbitMQ            : order-created delivered
###   - payment-service     : Received OrderCreated → published PaymentCompleted
###   - inventory + notification: full chain still fires
###
### Before Lesson 15 this would have left an orphaned order with no
### downstream processing.

POST {{orderService}}/orders/chaos
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "orderId": "ORD-CHAOS-2",
    "amount": 42
}